      • onCondition

        public GetCurrentUrlSupplier onCondition​(java.util.function.Predicate<java.lang.String> condition)
        When it is expected that current url should be changed/suitable to some criteria then it is possible to define some described condition. It waits for time defined by WaitingProperties.WAITING_FOR_PAGE_LOADED_DURATION or waitFor(Duration). If current url is not matched the criteria after defined time then IllegalStateException is thrown.
        Parameters:
        condition - is a criteria than current url should meet.
        Returns:
        self-reference.

      • waitFor

        public GetCurrentUrlSupplier waitFor​(java.time.Duration waitFor)
        When it is expected that current url should be changed/suitable to some criteria then it is possible to define some described condition. It waits for time defined by the method. It has sense when some condition is defined by onCondition(Predicate).
        Parameters:
        waitFor - is time to wait for current url meets some criteria defined by onCondition(Predicate)
        Returns:
        self-reference.
